      "description": "create-file-from-base64 wrote raw bytes (payload includes NUL and 0xFF — invalid utf8, so this proves binary-safe write) and get-file-base64's independent read re-encoded to the identical literal. Checked in-bot (crumb) and out-of-band ($var equals literal).",
